Kendi POS — Backend
Spring Boot + PostgreSQL REST API for **Kendi POS**, a point-of-sale system designed for Kosovo cafes and restaurants.

 Tech Stack

- Java 21 + Spring Boot 3.5
- PostgreSQL 16 (Docker)
- Spring Data JPA + Hibernate
- Spring Security** with BCrypt password hashing
- Maven build tool

 Features

- 🔐 PIN-based authentication with BCrypt hashing
- 📋 Full CRUD for Categories, Products, Tables, Staff, Orders
- 💰 Multi-order support per table with split payment
- 📊 Z-Report endpoint with daily revenue analytics
- 👥 Per-staff sales reports
- 🔄 Order state machine: open → closed → paid / cancelled
- 🌐 CORS configured for multi-device LAN access

API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Login with PIN |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | `/api/staff` | Staff management |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | `/api/categories` | Menu categories |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | `/api/products` | Menu products |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | `/api/tables` | Restaurant tables |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | `/api/orders` | Order management |
| POST | `/api/orders/{id}/close` | Close order |
| POST | `/api/orders/{id}/pay` | Pay single order |
| POST | `/api/orders/table/{id}/pay-all` | Pay all orders for table |
| GET | `/api/reports/z-report?date=...` | Daily Z-Report |
| GET | `/api/reports/staff?staffId=...` | Per-staff report |
| GET | `/api/reports/history` | Order history |

Getting Started
Prerequisites
- Java 21+
- Docker Desktop
- Maven (or use included `mvnw`)

#Setup

1. Start PostgreSQL with Docker:
bash
docker run --name kendi-db -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=kendi123 -e POSTGRES_DB=kendi_pos -p 5432:5432 -d postgres:16


2. Run the application:
bash
./mvnw spring-boot:run


3. Backend will be available at `http://localhost:8080`

 Default Login Credentials (seeded automatically)
- Admin: PIN `0000`
- Cashier: PIN `1234`

